l. 5. vos (sc. puellae) dicite eam quae laeta est fluviis. ‘Ye maidens sing of her who delights in rivers, and in the foliage of the woods, wherever it towers on cold Algidus‚' &c. Algidus was a range of mountains in Latium. Erymanthus was an Arcadian peak on the borders of Achaea and Elis. Cragus a spur of Mount Taurus in Lycia.
